org.jerkar.crypto.pgp
Class JkPgp

java.lang.Object
  org.jerkar.crypto.pgp.JkPgp

public final class JkPgp
extends java.lang.Object

Provides method for signing and verify signature with PGP.

When constructing JkPgp, you can provide a secret key ring, a public key ring or both.
Note that you need the secret ring for signing and the public ring for verifying.

sign

public void sign(java.io.File fileToSign,
                 java.io.File output,
                 java.lang.String password)
Signs the specified file with the first secret key of this key ring. The password is necessary if the secret key is protected.

Parameters:
fileToSign - The file to sign
output - The file where will be written the signature (no need to exist priorly)
password - password of the secret key
